Today, Apple operates 534 stores across 27 countries, with each location generating approximately &#36;5,500 per square foot annually â€“ among the highest in the retail industry. What began as a controversial gamble has become a cornerstone of Apple's success and a blueprint for experiential retail that competitors continue to emulate.<div class="linkback">Tag: <a href="https://www.macrumors.com/guide/retail/">Retail</a></div><br/>This article, &quot;<a href="https://www.macrumors.com/2025/05/19/apple-store-turns-24-today/">From Risky Bet to Retail Giant: Apple Store Turns 24 Today</a>&quot; first appeared on <a href="https://www.macrumors.com">MacRumors.com</a><br/><br/><a href="https://forums.macrumors.com/threads/from-risky-bet-to-retail-giant-apple-store-turns-24-today.2457324/">Discuss this article</a> in our forums<br/><br/>